@node Main "Labyzarre - Documentation"

                            'Labyzarre' 1.21

                           by Charles-N. Jacob

  'Labyzarre' is a Workbench @{" game " link play} played on a 10 by 10 grid, which
is surrounded by a wall. There are two doors: en entry door, located
at the top of the game area and an exit at the bottom of the grid.
The @{" goal " link play} is to go from the entry point to the exit, you must move
to every square of the grid and you cannot go to an already passed
square. When you move, a path will be drawn on the squares you
visited. The game ends if you 'trap' yourself in a dead-end (between
walls, blocks and/or already visited squares).

  The game features two playing mode, a @{" Normal " link play} (or 'practice')
game and a game with @{" Blocks " link play}, which you have to go around...

  Have fun!

