@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Labyzarre" where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries are
needed.

                             How to play?

  Playing Labyzarre is simple: you just have to go to the exit, but you
have to move on all the tiles on the board (except on the 'blocks', if
there are any).

  Your position is indicated by a smiling face icon, at the start of a
game it is located below the entry door. To move, just click on a square
next to your position (at left, right, down or up from where you are),
you can also move by using the cursor keys of the keyboard (or the 2, 4,
6 or 8 key on the numeric keypad to go down, left, right or up,
respectively). Your location will be displayed to the new position (if
the move is possible) and a path will be drawn where you originally were.

  You can't go to a square you already visited and the game ends when you
either successfully get to the exit or you 'trap' yourself in a dead-end
(between walls, blocks and/or already passed squares).

  In 'Labyzarre' there are two ways to play:

 -The @{b}Normal@{ub} game: The grid is empty, you have to move to every
                   square and get to the exit.

 -The @{b}Blocks@{ub} game: There are 10 blocks randomly placed in the game
                   area. You cannot move through a block, so you must go
                   around it and like the 'Normal' game, you have to pass
                   on every unoccupied square until you get to the exit.

  Have fun!

                                 OPTIONS

  In the game window, there are 3 buttons:

 -@{b}New Game@{ub}:      Restarts the game.

 -@{b}About...@{ub}:      Displays the informations about the game.

 -@{b}Normal/Blocks@{ub}: Toggles between the 'Normal' and the
                 'Blocks' game.

